# Proposal Writer — Orschell Excavating E-Commerce Full-Stack

## Deliverables produced

### 1. Cover letter (`cover-letter.md`)
- Hook: names their problem + outcome immediately, no filler opener
- Demo link in sentence 2 with admin credentials for instant access
- Concrete approach: codebase audit first, then layered feature implementation, Stripe as additive
- Proof: USBank TDAAS (solo SME, 60k LOC), Optum (PostgreSQL daily), TypeScript primary language
- Warm low-pressure close; github.com/mwegter95 (correct handle)
- Zero em/en dashes; no banned phrasing

### 2. One-pager (`one-pager.html`)
- Industrial design: #1C1F24 bg, #F76B10 orange accent, #FFD600 yellow, Barlow Condensed + Inter (matches demo)
- Sections: hero with live demo CTA + credentials, 6 feature cards (badges: Live / Mocked+labeled), 8 screenshot grid (customer + admin flows), 22 REST endpoint list with method color coding, tech stack (backend / frontend / DB design / production path), 3-week timeline with $1,700 price box, 4 proof-point bio grid, footer links
- All 8 posting requirements represented with traceability to live features
- Screenshots embedded as relative paths (same directory as screenshots)
- Responsive breakpoints at 640px

### 3. Deck (`deck.pptx`)  — 8 slides, 13.33 x 7.5 in
| Slide | Content |
|-------|---------|
| 1 | Title: split panel, demo URL + credentials on right |
| 2 | 8 requirements grid, each mapped to a live feature |
| 3 | Demo screenshots (home, shop, admin dashboard, admin products) with live URL |
| 4 | Tech stack: backend / frontend / DB / production Postgres path |
| 5 | Admin CMS screenshots (dashboard, products, orders, inventory) |
| 6 | 3-week timeline with price highlight bar |
| 7 | 4 proof-point cards (USBank, Optum, TypeScript, portfolio) |
| 8 | Close slide with demo link + credentials |

Design: BG #1C1F24, accent #F76B10, SURFACE #25292F, text #E8ECF0, muted #9BA3AD. Hazard stripe bars on title/close slides. Orange left-bar cards for credibility/stack sections. Real screenshots embedded.

## Key content decisions
- Mock payment: called out as "Mocked + labeled" badge in one-pager feature card and explicitly named in cover letter as "a Stripe integration would be a one-day addition"
- node:sqlite vs PostgreSQL: production migration path explained on one-pager and in deck slide 4; schema compatibility stated concretely (driver swap, no SQL changes)
- Admin credentials visible in all three deliverables so reviewer can immediately test the admin panel
- Timeline framed as "audit existing codebase first" (not "build from scratch") to match the posting which says site is already in development
- Price: $1,700 as posted, no negotiation hedge

